  </div>
</section>

<!-- ░░ STATS ░░ -->
<div class="stats">
  <div class="wrap stats-grid reveal">
    <div class="stat"><div class="num" data-count="4.2">4.2<span class="u">M+</span></div><div class="lbl">links monitored</div></div>
    <div class="stat"><div class="num" data-count="12000">12,000</div><div class="lbl">sites protected</div></div>
    <div class="stat"><div class="num">99.99<span class="u">%</span></div><div class="lbl">alert delivery</div></div>
    <div class="stat"><div class="num">&lt;30<span class="u">s</span></div><div class="lbl">time to alert</div></div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ░░ PROBLEM / 404 ░░ -->
<section id="problem">
  <div class="wrap problem-grid">
    <div class="reveal">
      <span class="eyebrow">The internet rots quietly</span>
      <h2 style="font-size:clamp(28px,3.6vw,42px);margin-top:16px">Links die. Servers hiccup. Nobody tells you.</h2>
      <p style="color:var(--muted);font-size:18px;margin-top:18px">Every site decays. A vendor moves a page, a deploy 500s, a cert expires at 2am. Your visitors hit the wall long before you ever notice, and most of them simply leave.</p>
      <div class="pains">
        <div class="pain"><span class="x">✗</span><span><b>Dead links bleed trust &amp; SEO.</b> Google demotes pages full of 404s, and shoppers don't come back after a broken checkout.</span></div>
        <div class="pain"><span class="x">✗</span><span><b>Outages hide in plain sight.</b> The average downtime goes unnoticed for 90+ minutes when no one is watching.</span></div>
        <div class="pain"><span class="x">✗</span><span><b>Manual checks don't scale.</b> You can't click every link on every page, every day, forever.</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="reveal">
      <div class="win404">
        <div class="bar">
          <span class="traf" style="background:#FF5F57"></span>
          <span class="traf" style="background:#FEBC2E"></span>
          <span class="traf" style="background:#28C840"></span>
          <span class="title">Not Found · Mozilla</span>
        </div>
        <div class="body">
          <div class="code">404</div>
          <div class="msg">The page you requested could not be found.</div>
          <div class="url">https://yoursite.com/the-link-you-forgot-about</div>
          <div class="tag">🐤 LinkCanary would've caught this 3 weeks ago</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ░░ FEATURES ░░ -->
<section id="features">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="sec-head center reveal">
      <span class="eyebrow" style="justify-content:center">Everything in one perch</span>
      <h2>Keep every link alive and every page online</h2>
      <p>One lightweight canary watches your whole web presence, from the homepage to the deepest outbound link.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="feat-grid">
      <div class="card reveal">
        <div class="ic g"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M3 12h4l2 6 4-14 2 8h6"/></svg></div>
        <h3>Uptime monitoring</h3>
        <p>Checks your sites and endpoints as often as every 30 seconds, from multiple regions, so a blip in one location never fools you.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card reveal">
        <div class="ic r"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M9 17H7A5 5 0 0 1 7 7h2"/><path d="M15 7h2a5 5 0 0 1 .5 9.97"/><line x1="8" y1="12" x2="11" y2="12"/></svg></div>
        <h3>Broken-link crawling</h3>
        <p>Crawls your entire site on a schedule and flags every 404, dead redirect, and rotten outbound link, internal and external.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card reveal">
        <div class="ic y"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M18 8A6 6 0 0 0 6 8c0 7-3 9-3 9h18s-3-2-3-9"/><path d="M13.7 21a2 2 0 0 1-3.4 0"/></svg></div>
        <h3>Instant alerts</h3>
        <p>Email, Slack, Discord, SMS, PagerDuty, or webhook. Know within seconds, with the exact URL, status code, and screenshot.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card reveal">
        <div class="ic b"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="3" y="4" width="18" height="14" rx="2"/><path d="M3 9h18"/><circle cx="7" cy="6.5" r=".6" fill="currentColor"/></svg></div>
        <h3>Public status pages</h3>
        <p>Beautiful hosted status pages on your own domain that keep customers informed and cut support tickets during incidents.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card reveal">
        <div class="ic v"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 2 4 6v6c0 5 3.5 8 8 10 4.5-2 8-5 8-10V6z"/><path d="m9 12 2 2 4-4"/></svg></div>
        <h3>SSL &amp; domain expiry</h3>
        <p>Get warned weeks before a TLS certificate or domain registration lapses, so you never get caught by a surprise expiry again.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card reveal">
        <div class="ic y"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M3 3v18h18"/><path d="M7 14l3-4 3 3 5-7"/></svg></div>
        <h3>History &amp; insights</h3>
        <p>Response-time graphs, incident timelines, and shareable uptime &amp; SLA reports. Proof of reliability, ready to export.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ░░ HOW IT WORKS ░░ -->
<section id="how" style="background:rgba(255,255,255,.012);border-top:1px solid var(--border-soft);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-soft)">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="sec-head center reveal">
      <span class="eyebrow" style="justify-content:center">Live in three minutes</span>
      <h2>Set it, and let the canary sing</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="steps">
      <svg class="arrow a1" width="78" height="34" viewBox="0 0 78 34" fill="none"><path d="M2 22 C 22 6, 44 6, 64 18" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.4" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-dasharray="2 7"/><path d="M58 11 L66 19 L55 21 Z" fill="currentColor"/></svg>
      <svg class="arrow a2" width="78" height="34" viewBox="0 0 78 34" fill="none"><path d="M2 16 C 22 28, 44 28, 64 12" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.4" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-dasharray="2 7"/><path d="M58 19 L66 11 L67 22 Z" fill="currentColor"/></svg>
      <div class="step reveal">
        <div class="n">1</div>
        <h3>Add your URLs</h3>
        <p>Drop in a domain, paste a sitemap, or connect a repo. LinkCanary maps every page and link automatically.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="step reveal">
        <div class="n">2</div>
        <h3>We watch, 24/7</h3>
        <p>Our canaries ping your pages, endpoints, links, and certs on your schedule, from data centers worldwide.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="step reveal">
        <div class="n">3</div>
        <h3>You get chirped</h3>
        <p>The instant something breaks, you get a precise alert where you already work, before a visitor ever notices.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ░░ LIVE DEMO TERMINAL ░░ -->
<section id="demo">
  <div class="wrap demo-grid">
    <div class="reveal">
      <span class="eyebrow">See it in action</span>
      <h2 style="font-size:clamp(28px,3.6vw,42px);margin-top:16px">A watchful eye that never blinks</h2>
      <p style="color:var(--muted);font-size:18px;margin-top:18px">This is LinkCanary running live checks against a real site. Healthy responses scroll by quietly. The moment a link rots, the canary sounds off.</p>
      <div class="demo-points">
        <div class="dp"><span class="c">✓</span><span><b>Multi-region checks</b> confirm an outage is real before alerting, no false alarms at 3am.</span></div>
        <div class="dp"><span class="c">✓</span><span><b>Full request context</b>: status code, latency, redirect chain, and a screenshot attached to every incident.</span></div>
        <div class="dp"><span class="c">✓</span><span><b>Auto-resolve</b> closes the incident and tells you the moment the link is healthy again.</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="reveal">
      <div class="term">
        <div class="bar">
          <span class="traf" style="background:#FF5F57"></span>
          <span class="traf" style="background:#FEBC2E"></span>
          <span class="traf" style="background:#28C840"></span>
          <span class="title">canary@watchtower: ~/acme.com</span>
          <span class="right"><span class="dot"></span>watching</span>
        </div>
        <div class="scr" id="term"></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ░░ PRICING ░░ -->
