        <div class="pdesc">The full tool, running on your own machine or server.</div>
        <ul>
          <li><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="m5 12 5 5L20 7"/></svg>Uptime &amp; broken-link monitoring</li>
          <li><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="m5 12 5 5L20 7"/></svg>Scheduled crawls of your whole site</li>
          <li><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="m5 12 5 5L20 7"/></svg>Slack, email &amp; webhook alerts</li>
          <li><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="m5 12 5 5L20 7"/></svg>SSL &amp; domain-expiry checks</li>
          <li><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="m5 12 5 5L20 7"/></svg>Self-hosted, so your data never leaves your servers</li>
        </ul>
        <a href="https://github.com/LinkCanary/LinkCanary" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn btn-primary">Get it on GitHub →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p style="text-align:center;color:var(--dim);font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:12.5px;margin-top:28px">MIT licensed · Star us on GitHub · Contributions welcome</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ░░ FAQ ░░ -->
<section id="faq">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="sec-head center reveal">
      <span class="eyebrow" style="justify-content:center">Questions, answered</span>
      <h2>Everything you might ask</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="faq">
      <details class="reveal" open><summary>How often does LinkCanary check my links?<span class="pm">+</span></summary><div class="ans">As often as every 30 seconds on paid plans, and every 5 minutes on the free plan. You can set different intervals per monitor: tight checks for your checkout flow, relaxed ones for your blog archive.</div></details>
      <details class="reveal"><summary>What exactly can it monitor?<span class="pm">+</span></summary><div class="ans">Websites and landing pages, API endpoints, internal and outbound links, redirects, SSL certificates, domain expiry, keyword presence (e.g. "is the word ‘checkout’ still on the page?"), and specific status codes. If it speaks HTTP, the canary can watch it.</div></details>
      <details class="reveal"><summary>How do alerts reach me?<span class="pm">+</span></summary><div class="ans">Email, Slack, Discord, SMS, PagerDuty, Microsoft Teams, or any webhook. Every alert includes the failing URL, status code, response time, region, and a screenshot. We auto-notify you again the moment it recovers.</div></details>
      <details class="reveal"><summary>Is there really a free plan?<span class="pm">+</span></summary><div class="ans">Yes. 50 checks free, forever, no credit card required. It's perfect for personal sites and side-projects, and you can upgrade the moment you need tighter intervals or more channels.</div></details>
      <details class="reveal"><summary>Can I monitor staging or password-protected sites?<span class="pm">+</span></summary><div class="ans">Absolutely. Add custom request headers, basic-auth credentials, or bearer tokens per monitor, and LinkCanary will check authenticated and internal environments just like production.</div></details>
      <details class="reveal"><summary>How is this different from Google Search Console?<span class="pm">+</span></summary><div class="ans">Search Console reports problems days later, only for pages Google has crawled. LinkCanary checks <em>your</em> links on <em>your</em> schedule and alerts you in seconds, covering uptime, APIs, SSL, and outbound links that Search Console never touches.</div></details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ░░ FINAL CTA ░░ -->
<section style="padding-top:30px">
  <div class="wrap reveal">
    <div class="cta-band">
